{"article_id":"InHLckTs9nwMheLx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Benghazi investigative committee on Tuesday formally requested","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that former Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton give a transcribed interview","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"detailing her decision-making","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"in determining which emails she turned over to the government","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"and why she wiped her email server clean .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"Chairman Trey Gowdy , South Carolina Republican , made the request","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"as the State Department began to divulge some of Mrs. Clinton ' s emails","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"that she hid for years .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"One of the early messages contradicts her claim","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that she wanted to use a single electronic device for email .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Mr. Gowdy said","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Mrs. Clinton ' s \" unique arrangement with herself \"","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"- in which she claimed complete control of government business email -","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"needs to be explained ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and nobody other than Mrs. Clinton can do that .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"The interview would be behind closed doors","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"but would be part of the committee investigation ' s record .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"A public hearing would be held","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"once the select investigative committee has gathered all of the documents","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"it believes","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"it needs ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"Mr. Gowdy said in a letter to Mrs. Clinton ' s attorney .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"\" We continue to believe","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Secretary Clinton ' s email arrangement with herself is highly unusual , if not unprecedented , \"","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"\" The decision","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"to delete these records during the pendency of a congressional investigation","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"only exacerbates our need","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"to better understand what the secretary did , when she did it , and why she did it .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"While she has cited a variety of justifications for this arrangement ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"many questions and details about the arrangement remain unanswered . \"","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Mr. Gowdy said","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"the questions include why Mrs. Clinton refused a government-issued account","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"and set up her own account and server ;","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"why she kept the emails herself","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"rather than turning them over to the State Department","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"when she left office in early 2013 ;","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"and how she decided which of the 62,000 emails from her time in office she would delete ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"and which she would turn over .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"The chairman also pointedly made clear","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"since the emails are under committee investigation ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"any action","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"to destroy them","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"would be illegal .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"that is why Mrs. Clinton must turn over her server to a neutral third party","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"- a request","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Mrs. Clinton ' s team has rejected ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"she already has complied with the law .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Clinton spokesman Nick Merrill said","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"Mrs. Clinton looks forward to a public hearing ,","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"but he didn ' t address Mr. Gowdy ' s request for a transcribed interview .","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"\" Secretary Clinton already told the committee months ago","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"that she was ready to appear at a public hearing .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"It is by their choice","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"that hasn ' t happened , \"","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Mr. Merrill said .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"\" To be clear ,","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"she remains ready to appear at a hearing","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"open to the American public . \"","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"The White House ,","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"which has tried to keep the Clinton email situation at arm ' s length ,","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"waved off questions about the Benghazi committee ' s request ,","depth":4},{"id":65,"text":"saying","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"it is up to Mrs. Clinton ,","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"who","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"spokesman Josh Earnest made clear","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"is no longer part of the Obama administration .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"\" If the committee makes a request","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"and Secretary Clinton , in her capacity as a private citizen , decides","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"that she wants to - once again - go above and beyond in terms of trying to provide them information and access ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"then that will be a decision for her to make , \"","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"Mr . Earnest said .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"Mrs. Clinton said","depth":3},{"id":76,"text":"she used an email server","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"she set up at her home in New York ,","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"and issued herself her own email address ,","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"because she wanted to use a single device and account for both personal and private mail .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"She has said","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"she determined","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"that about 30,000 of her 62,000 emails from her time in office were government-related ,","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"and in December","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"- nearly two years after she left office -","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"she turned those over to the State Department amid prodding by the Benghazi committee .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"The emails","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"she turned over","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"amounted to 55,000 pages .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"The State Department said this week","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"that it will take several months to process those emails","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"because it needs to scan the pages","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"to create digital files","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"and then needs to run them by authorities","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"to determine what can be released publicly .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"In a court filing this week , the Obama administration said","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"it wants to rush production of all of those emails online","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"and rejected a request from a conservative legal group , Judicial Watch , for a quick turnaround on an open-records request .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"The State Department didn ' t apply that to all requests .","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"The Associated Press reported Tuesday morning","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"that the department had released four of Mrs. Clinton ' s emails to the news organization","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"- including one","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that showed","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"Mrs. Clinton used an iPad in addition to her mobile phone","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"for sending emails .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"That contradicts one of Mrs. Clinton ' s justifications","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"for having a single account .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"The former first lady and potential Democratic presidential candidate told reporters in early March","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"that she didn ' t want to carry multiple devices .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"Judicial Watch has multiple outstanding requests for Clinton emails .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"Its president , Tom Fitton , said","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"the State Department has searched Mrs. Clinton ' s emails in one of those requests","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"and will divulge the results to the group Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"\" It is not a matter of playing favorites ;","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"it is a matter of further harming","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"[ through delay ]","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"our right","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"to know under the Freedom of Information Act ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"which the agency has trashed , \"","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"Mr. Fitton said .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":239,"left":194,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":181,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":170,"right":180,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":141,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":129,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":124,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":0,"right":123,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":1,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":2,"right":121,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":128,"left":126,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":5,"right":125,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":133,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS